article.headline: N. Dakota St. 68, Centenary 53
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Brett Winkelman had 26 points and 14 rebounds Saturday to lead North Dakota State to a 68-53 Summit League win over Centenary. Winkelman also had three assists and three steals. He was one of three Bison (6-2, 2-0) players scoring in double figures. Ben Woodside had 18 points and six assists and Mike Nelson added 10 points. The Bison were up 33-24 at the half and led 40-38 with 11:47 left to play in the game. But they went on a 25-10 run to take control. NDSU shot 45 percent from the field and outrebounded the Gents 46-27. Centenary (2-8, 0-2) shot just 34 percent from the field and 30 percent in the second half. The Gents got 11 points from Nick Stallings and 10 from Chase Adams, who also added six assists.
